UNALLOCATED PENSION AND OTHER POSTRETIREMENT BENEFIT EXPENSE

UNALLOCATED PENSION AND OTHER POSTRETIREMENT BENEFIT EXPENSE REPRESENTS THE PORTION OF PENSION AND OTHER POSTRETIREMENT BENEFIT COSTS THAT ARE NOT RECOGNIZED BY BUSINESS SEGMENTS FOR SEGMENT REPORTING PURPOSES. PENSION COSTS, COMPRISING

GENERALLY ACCEPTED ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA

(

GAAP

) SERVICE AND PRIOR SERVICE COSTS, ARE ALLOCATED TO COMMERCIAL AIRPLANES. PENSION COSTS ARE ALLOCATED TO BDS USING

U.S. GOVERNMENT COST ACCOUNTING STANDARDS

(

CAS

), WHICH EMPLOY DIFFERENT ACTUARIAL ASSUMPTIONS AND ACCOUNTING CONVENTIONS THAN

GAAP

. THESE COSTS ARE ALLOCABLE TO GOVERNMENT CONTRACTS. OTHER POSTRETIREMENT BENEFIT COSTS ARE ALLOCATED TO BUSINESS SEGMENTS BASED ON

CAS

, WHICH IS GENERALLY BASED ON BENEFITS PAID.

